SIMPLE: pharaoh
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharaoh
<hw>Pha"raoh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>par⟦omac⟧h</ets>; of Egyptian origin: cf. L. <ets>pharao</ets>, Gr.
<grk>faraw`</grk>. Cf. <er>Faro</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A title by
which the sovereigns of ancient Egypt were designated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Faro</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pharaoh's chicken</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
gier-eagle, or Egyptian vulture; -- so called because often sculpured on
Egyptian monuments. It is nearly white in color.</cd> --
<col><b>Pharaoh's rat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the common
ichneumon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharaon</ent>⟦br⟧
